snippet.textDisplay: This comes off super pretentious to me. Maybe it's because there's not much context here, maybe there were dealings that fell through or some bad blood behind the scenes, but all I'm seeing here is a company sending free gifts to someone else and just because the company didn't do their research the recipient of free things is upset it's not personalized. Just don't give them attention if you don't appreciate their gifts. Donate their gift to someone else, don't mention them on youtube, and continue making other videos. I'd fucking love some free things. I'm sure there are millions of others who would love free things. It's fine you don't like the gifts, just tell them as such and let them know they aren't getting any publicity from you unless they do better.  This is the same ego that made me not enjoy your bon appetit video. It's toxic and hard to watch. You're a legitimately funny person and a seemingly decent person, but you also have a lot of growing up to do.
